Well my new years was definitely one to remember. I had been feeling great on the bike lately training out at @his956facility prepping for the up coming season. Unfortunately on Saturday I had an accident with my brakes fading on the face of a jump causing me to over jump by 30ft falling straight from the air to flat. After the initial impact my left arm came off and I launched off the berm into a dirt retaining wall smashing my head into the bars splitting my chin open and pushing my neck back hard enough to break my C2 in 2 places.

To say I am lucky to still be here is an understatement. The doctors were shocked to see the X-rays and the fact I had been able to walk to the car and be driven to hospital with no serious after effects! (I didn’t know I broke my neck 😬). Thankfully they’ve decided not to fuse it, we just can’t take this collar off for a while lol. 

Other than the broken neck, I suffered a chin laceration all the way down to the bone which is stitched back up. I had partially collapsed both lungs and also broke my radius in the left arm in 5 places which is now plated and wired back together. We spent a few days in the ICU and finally got to get settled at home 😁.

I am so incredibly grateful to still be here today writing this and I can not thank everyone enough for all the support and kind words I have received over the past few days! ❤️ It is going to be a long road back to full health, but I feel like it’s a miracle I’m still here and without any deficits, so we’re going to make the most of every second after this 🙌🏼

With my beautiful fiancé going through the worst year with her illness and then adding this on top to cap it off, it is definitely hard mentally to process, but that’s what life is about right? We are challenged to show who we really are and what we can do. We will heal and be stronger than ever on the other side! 💪🏼

TMFJ will be WALKING down the aisle to @alliespurgeon in a neck brace in 9 days 🥹💍❤️

If you want to become a more confident, safer rider and take your racing to the next level, check out @buildingchampionsacademy 💪🏼. No matter your skill level, at BCA we cover all of the basics to the most advance techniques while working with you personally to improve at your pace!

There is no greater honour than putting on the green and gold colours of the Aussie jersey 🙌🏼.

I am super excited to say I will be competing in my 9th ISDE (man I feel old 😅) this year in Argentina! 
To make it even better, I get to go alongside my long time team mate @missjessgardiner, who combined we have a total of 18 ISDEs under our belts and 6 world titles 🤯! Joining us will be newcomer @danielle_261_ ,who is starting in the shoes Jess and I once stood in and who I am honoured to share all the knowledge we have learnt over the years with. 

It has been a huge effort this year to make the ISDE with funding and logistical issues, but the Women’s team dug deep and we will be flying the flag for all of us as we head to Argentina in October. 

We as a team, are as motivated as ever to show the world what Aussies are made of and we NEED your support now more than ever! 

Please show your support on our Aussie girls Go Fund Me page, every little bit helps and we are immensely grateful for everything. 
check out the link in my bio 🇦🇺🦘
